s to power. Clarifying the themes and challenges of the Chilean women's movement today, she finds an inextricable link between women's struggles for citizenship rights and the nation's broader struggles for democracy and social justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFeminismxChile. 0aFeminismzChile. 0aFemmes en politiquexHistoirexChili. 0aFemmes et démocratiexChili. 0aFemmes et démocratiexChili. 0aFéminismexChili. 0aFéminismexChili. 0aWomen and democracyxChile. 0aWomen and democracyzChile. 0aWomenxPolitical activityxHistoryxChile. 0aWomenxPolitical activityzChilexHistory. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078425140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978162637161340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781626371613423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781626371613/original  a978-3-11-078425-1  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK